captions.text:
Day of The JV/Varsity Scrimmage
Two Hours Remain
Huh, you draw in the notes section too?

Oh, I'm just writing a little not
to give to Jenny after the scrim.

or anything like that.
I mean, she totally has a boyfriend
let's be friends" sort of note.

Oh. I like to draw extra
lines to make it graph paper.
Yo Brian, man. Kick ass out there.
I will give it my best shot.

Good, cause we have two weeks
allowance on you beating The Law.

Alright. Settle down.
Settle down people. Settle down.

I am proud to be your TA
for rhythm gaming this year

Something you two losers in the back
could stand to learn something about.
# I present to you, the sultan of shred #

# the raddest dad, #
# with the baddest ad... itude. #

Thats all right.
That's why you took this class.
To learn from the best, me,
Give the people what they want.
They want to be you while they do you.

Cause if you don't give the people
what they want, they'll divorce you,
they'll take your sweet dirt bike,

and they'll leave you with
a no good loser for a son.
Grip the steering wheel of destiny!

Ted, are you sure you are ok, man?
That was, like, really rough.
100% Big D. I just gotta refuel.

Well, I have to get to
scrimmage, buddy. But...

Ki can you take care of
him for a little while?

Don't worry about me.
Good dad out there.

End of Seventh Period
One Hour Remains

The Law Vs Brian D
Justice will be served

I'll get to everybody, I'll get to
everybody. Hold your horses. Calm down.
Hey! Give me twenty big ones on Brian D.
Alright, a risk taker, huh? I like that.
There you go. Who's next? Who's next?

What ya got? What ya got? I'll take yeah.
I'll make your bet for ya.

That's fine with me. What ya want?
Ten on Law. There ya go. Boom.

Hey man. Look, I was thinking,
maybe you can just do some fancy foot work

or caps lock and run away
when you're out there.

Cause I am betting you can make it at
least three minutes against The Law.
Say hi to The Law for me, Brian.

The Junior Varsity Pre-Game
Meeting - Thirty Minutes Remain -

I want to see those
grenade skills in action.

And as for the little
freshman that could,
stay tight and out of sight.

Yeah. Isn't this scrimmage just an excuse
for your boyfriend to pad his kill reel.
Varsity is out there to show off.
We. We're out there to kick ass.

and we're gonna wipe the
smirk right off their faces.

that maggot isn't gonna talk to me for
a week after we're through with him!

Alright. See you on the
battlefield. Dismissed.

Nope. I just thought you
might want to check this out.

And uh, you might want to check
out the notes section. B-t-dubs.
But I have to stay focused right now.
If you ever want to get unfocused...
This is team CTF, not a deathmatch.
You follow my orders, you'll be fine.

Brian's Private Pre-Game Pump Up
Five MInutes Remain
Jenny wants you to avoid The Law.

They won't even know
I'm there. Ninja style.

He made a whole soda can
disappear in my mouth.

Speaking of dead meat, what was Jenny
thinking putting BrianD on her team?
She was probably thinking I'm awesome.

Wait. You told her to
put him on the team?

Cause while I love a well
earned victory burg,
what I really love, more than anything,

That big baby Brian is
bound to burn, bro.
but a worthless, no talent fluke.

- What's he doing?
- Costing me five hundred bucks!

Brian, I am going to the intel.
Get to that structure and cover me.

You know, I think I will just stick
back here and nade spam, sir.
Damnit Brian, what is your malfunction?

Is The Law going to be
waiting for me up there?
Follow my orders, or get off my team.
Give the people what they want.
